gt.blockmachines.cable.desc=Max Voltage: %s\nMax Amperage: %s\nLoss/Meter/Ampere: %s
gt.blockmachines.gt_frame.desc.format=Just something you can put covers on.
gt.blockmachines.transformer.desc=%s -> %s (Use Soft Mallet to invert)
gt.blockmachines.transformer_advanced.desc=Accepts %sA and outputs %sA\nToggle 2A/8A half-mode with Screwdriver
gt.blockmachines.bronze_hull.desc=For your first Steam Machines
gt.blockmachines.highpressure_hull.desc=For improved Steam Machines
gt.blockmachines.basic_hull.desc=§rYou just need §5I§dm§4a§cg§ei§an§ba§3t§9i§1o§5n§r to use this.
gt.blockmachines.long_distance_item_pipeline.desc=Sends items over long distances
gt.blockmachines.long_distance_fluid_pipeline.desc=Sends fluids over long distances
gt.blockmachines.long_distance_pipeline.desc=Only one Input and Output are allowed per pipeline\nOnly Input and Output have to be chunkloaded\nTransfer rate is solely limited by input rate\nMinimum distance: %s blocks
gt.blockmachines.dynamo_hatch.desc=Generating electric Energy from Multiblocks\nPuts out up to 1 Amp
gt.blockmachines.dynamo_hatch_buffer.desc=Dynamo with internal storage and additional Amp capacity\nDoes not accept more than %sEU/t as input
gt.blockmachines.energy_hatch.desc=Energy Injector for Multiblocks\nAccepts up to 2 Amps
gt.blockmachines.energy_hatch_wireless.desc=§7Stores energy globally in a network, up to 2^(2^31) EU.\n§7Does not connect to wires. This block withdraws EU from the network.
gt.blockmachines.energy_hatch_debug.desc=§7Buffers EU internally\n§7Configure Amps and Voltage in the UI\n§o/gt global_energy_set Develo-... begone!
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch.desc=Fluid Input for Multiblocks\nRight click with screwdriver to toggle input filter\nCapacity: %s L
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_multislot.desc=Fluid Input for Multiblocks\nCapacity: %s L\nCan hold %s types of fluid.
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_generator.desc=Fluid Input for Multiblocks\nCapacity: %s L\nHatch Tier: %s
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_generator.airintake.desc=§cDO NOT OBSTRUCT THE INPUT!\nDraws in Air from the surrounding environment\nCreates %s of Air every %s ticks
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_generator.atmosphere.desc=§cDO NOT OBSTRUCT THE INPUT!\nDraws in Air from the surrounding environment\nCompletelly fills up every %s ticks
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_generator.reservoir.desc=Infinite water supply hatch\nFills to max capacity every 5 seconds
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_me.desc=Machine Type: §eSIH§r\nAdvanced fluid input for Multiblocks\nHatch Tier: %s\nRetrieves directly from ME\nKeeps 16 fluid types in stock\nChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter.\nConfiguration data can be copy/pasted using a data stick.
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_me.autopull.desc=Machine Type: §eASIH§r\nNext-gen fluid input for Multiblocks\nHatch Tier: %s\nRetrieves directly from ME\nKeeps 16 fluid types in stock\nAuto-Pull from ME mode will automatically stock the first\n16 fluid in the ME system, updated every 5 seconds.\nToggle by right-clicking with screwdriver, or use the GUI.\nUse the GUI to limit the minimum stack size for Auto-Pulling,\nadjust the slot refresh timer and enable fast recipe checks.\nWARNING: Fast recipe checks can be laggy. Use with caution.\nChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter.\nConfiguration data can be copy/pasted using a data stick.
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_solidifier.desc=Fluid Input with Mold for §eFluid Shaper§r\nCapacity: %s L
gt.blockmachines.input_hatch_debug.desc=§7Stocks Fluids internally\n§7Configure Fluids in the UI\n§7Configured Fluids will not be consumed in processing\n§oWho knew it was this easy???
gt.blockmachines.output_hatch.desc=Fluid Output for Multiblocks\nCapacity: %s L\nRight click with screwdriver to restrict output\nCan be restricted to put out Items and/or Steam/No Steam/1 specific Fluid\nRestricted Output Hatches are given priority for Multiblock Fluid output
gt.blockmachines.output_hatch_antimatter.desc=Fluid Output for Multiblocks\nStores Antimatter\nAntimatter can be inserted from any side\nFront face input can be toggled with a screwdriver\nCapacity: 16,384,000L
gt.blockmachines.output_hatch_me.desc=Fluid Output for Multiblocks\nStores directly into ME\nCan cache up to 128kL of fluids by default\nChange cache size by inserting a fluid storage cell\nChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter\nPartition the inserted Storage Cell to filter accepted outputs
gt.blockmachines.output_hatch_void.desc=Voids fluids from Multiblocks\nMust be configured to work\nMimics behavior of restricted hatches
gt.blockmachines.input_bus.desc=Item Input for Multiblocks\nShift + right click with screwdriver to turn Sort mode on/off\nCapacity: %s stacks
gt.blockmachines.input_bus.singular.desc=Item Input for Multiblocks\nShift + right click with screwdriver to turn Sort mode on/off\nCapacity: %s stack
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_chisel.desc=Item Input Bus for §eIndustrial Chisel§r\n%s + 1  Slots
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_crafting_me.desc=Machine Type: §eCRIB§r\nAdvanced item input for Multiblocks\nHatch Tier: %s\nProcesses patterns directly from ME\n%sChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter\nIgnores the contents of other buses or hatches\nAlso ignores other patterns within the same bus
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_crafting_me.support_fluid.desc=It supports patterns including fluids
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_crafting_me.not_support_fluid.desc=It does not support patterns including fluids
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_crafting_slave.desc=Proxy for Crafting Input Buffer/Bus (CRIB)\nHatch Tier: %s\nLink with Crafting Input Buffer/Bus using Data Stick to share inventory\nLeft click on the Crafting Input Buffer/Bus, then right click on this block to link them
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_me.desc=Machine Type: §eSIB§r\nNext-gen item input for Multiblocks\nHatch Tier: %s\nRetrieves directly from ME\nKeeps 16 item types in stock\nChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter.\nConfiguration data can be copy/pasted using a data stick.
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_me.autopull.desc=Machine Type: §eASIB§r\nAdvanced item input for Multiblocks\nHatch Tier: %s\nRetrieves directly from ME\nKeeps 16 item types in stock\nAuto-Pull from ME mode will automatically stock the first\n16 items in the ME system, updated every 5 seconds.\nToggle by right-clicking with screwdriver, or use the GUI.\nUse the GUI to limit the minimum stack size for Auto-Pulling,\nadjust the slot refresh timer and enable fast recipe checks.\nWARNING: Fast recipe checks can be laggy. Use with caution.\nChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter.\nConfiguration data can be copy/pasted using a data stick.
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_lens.desc=Holds a lens for UV laser focusing.
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_steam.desc=Item Input for Steam Multiblocks\nShift + right click with screwdriver to toggle automatic item shuffling\nCapacity: 4 stacks\nDoes not work with non-steam multiblocks
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_super.desc=Item Input for Multiblocks\n%s Slots
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_turbine.desc=An automation port for Large Turbines\nWill attempt once per 1200 ticks to fill the turbine slot of it's parent turbine\nYou may adjust this with a screwdriver\nHold shift to adjust in finer amounts\nHold control to adjust direction\nLeft Click with Screwdriver to reset\nThis module assumes the entire turbine is in the same Chunk
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_linked.desc=%s slot input bus linked together wirelessly\nLink does not cross world boundary\nLeft/right click with data stick to copy/paste configuration\nAdded by §6GigaGram§rFab
gt.blockmachines.input_bus_debug.desc=§7Stocks Items internally\n§7Configure Items in the UI\n§7Configured Items will not be consumed in processing\n§oWho knew it was this easy???
gt.blockmachines.output_bus.desc=Item Output for Multiblocks\nCapacity: %s stacks\nLeft click with data stick to save filter config\nRight click with data stick to load filter config
gt.blockmachines.output_bus.singular.desc=Item Output for Multiblocks\nCapacity: %s stack\nLeft click with data stick to save filter config\nRight click with data stick to load filter config
gt.blockmachines.output_bus_me.desc=Item Output for Multiblocks\nStores directly into ME\nCan cache 1600 items by default\nChange cache size by inserting a storage cell\nChange ME connection behavior by right-clicking with wire cutter\nPartition the inserted Storage Cell to filter accepted outputs
gt.blockmachines.output_bus_steam.desc=Item Output for Steam Multiblocks\nDoes not automatically export items\nCapacity: 4 stacks\nDoes not work with non-steam multiblocks
gt.blockmachines.output_bus_void.desc=Voids items from Multiblocks\nMust be configured to work
gt.blockmachines.output_bus_super.desc=Item Output for Multiblocks\n%s Slots\nLeft click with data stick to save filter config\nRight click with data stick to load filter config
gt.blockmachines.muffler.desc=Outputs the Pollution (Might cause ... things)\nDO NOT OBSTRUCT THE OUTPUT!\nReduces Pollution to %s%%
gt.blockmachines.boiler.solar.desc=Steam Power by the Sun\nProduces %sL of Steam per second\nCalcifies over time, reducing Steam output to %sL/s\nBreak and replace to descale
