gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.machinetype=Beam Crafter, Beam Assembler
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip1=Collides two beams of particles into target materials to modify
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip2=their subatomic structure
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip3=Input Beams can be supplied to either Beamline Input Hatch
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip4=Inputs are consumed immediately and will wait for particles
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip5=Up to §b%s§7 particles of each type can be buffered
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip6=Recipe progress is determined purely by particles consumed
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip7=from the buffer
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.tooltip8=Has §6%s§7 parallels
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamcrafter.dumpbuffer=Click to dump

gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beammirror.machinetype=Beam Mirror
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beammirror.tooltip1=Takes in particle beams and sends them back out
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beammirror.tooltip2=§6That's literally it.

gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamsplitter.machinetype=Beam Splitter
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamsplitter.machinetypefake=Beam Splitter, Bean Splitter
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamsplitter.tooltip1=Select which particles to blacklist in the output hatches
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamsplitter.tooltip2=Input particles will be split evenly among all valid output hatches

gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.machinetype=Beam Stabilizer
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip1=Accepts and stores up to 100000 §aParticles§7 from
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip2=potentially intermittent high §cRate§7 particle beam packets
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip3=and re-releases those particles as a stable beam at a
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip4=§cRate§7 of your choosing
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip5=If a particle beam with a different §aParticle§7, §6Energy§7 or
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip6=§bFocus§7 is sent to the machine during operation, it is
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.beamstabilizer.tooltip7=ignored UNLESS there are no currently stored §aParticles

gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.machinetype=Particle Accelerator, Particle Collider, LHC
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip1=Accelerates particles to high energies and then collides them to generate new particles
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip2=Electrically neutral particles are unaffected
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip3=Set the §etarget beam energy§7 (up to 2TeV) and the §9maximum number of cycles§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip4=Cycles every second
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip5=§f§nAccelerator mode§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip6=Accelerates the beam in the smaller LHC ring
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip7=Accelerator mode increases the §6Beam Energy§7 by §bEU Consumed in cycle§7 * §f0.1eV§7, until the
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip8=§eTarget Beam Energy§7 is reached, or the §9maximum number of cycles§7 is reached
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip9=If the §eTarget Beam Energy§7 is reached, multiply the current §cBeam Rate§7 by §f1.1§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip10=§aPower§7 cost starts at §f1A§7 of §fUV§7 per §cBeam Rate§7 and increases quadratically
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip11=with the §dnumber of completed cycles§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip12=§aP§7 = §f(1A UV)§7 * §cR§7 * §dN§7^2
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip13=Automatically switches to Collider mode when the §9maximum number of cycles§7 is reached
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip14=§f§nCollider mode§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip15=Splits the beam into §ftwo§7 beams that go in opposite directions in the larger LHC ring, which
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip16=then collide to generate new particles
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip17=The §3Collision Energy§7 is two times the §6Beam Energy§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip18=If the §3Collision Energy§7 exceeds the rest mass of a particle, that particle will start
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip19=appearing in the outputs
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip20=A particle output can only appear in the modules that correspond to the forces that
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip21=interact with that particle
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip22=For example, Neutrinos cannot appear in the Strong force module, §fALICE§7, since they do
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip23=not interact via the strong force
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip24=§fFiltered Beamline Output Hatches§7 will allow you to see the list of possible outputs, and
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip25=filter them
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip26=There are four LHC modules, marked by the letter on top of the module:
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip27=§bE - Electromagnetism§7 - Charged Matter Sensor (§bCMS§7)
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip28=§2W - Weak Interaction§7 - Advanced Total Lepton Assimilation Snare (§2ATLAS§7)
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip29=§fS - Strong Force§7 - Absolute Lattice Integrated Chromodynamic Encapsulator (§fALICE§7)
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beamcrafting.LHC.tooltip30=§5G - Gravity§7 - Localized Horizon Curvature Binder (§5LHCb§7)

